08/05/2007
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- The UN war crimes tribunal heard on Monday (May 7th) from the first witness in the trial against former Macedonian Interior Minister Ljube Boskovski and Johan Tarculovski, a former security official. 
They are facing charges for war crimes committed against ethnic Albanians in the village of Ljuboten during the 2001 conflict. 
Witness Zenap Jusufi, the mother of victim Rami Jusufi, was unable to identify the attackers at Monday's hearing, saying they had worn masks.
In other news Monday, three members of the "Shadow Wolves", an elite unit of Native American trackers from the United States, began a training course for Macedonia's border guards. 
It is aimed at better detecting smuggling and other types of illegal activity. 
(Vecer - 08/05/07; Makfax, MIA, A1 TV, Darik, Focus - 07/05/07)
